# 4. 伝説が生まれた場所

Kohane: Oh! Good morning, everyone!
An: Morning, Kohane!
Toya: Good morning. You're here early.
Kohane: Hm? We agreed to meet at eleven, right? But we're all here thirty minutes early...
An: I know why! We were all looking forward to today so much that we couldn't help but wake up early! Even Akito!
Akito: Hey, we're not little kids and this isn't some field trip.
Toya: Actually, she might not be far off.
Akito: Quiet, you... The point is that I never thought I'd get to see this place again.
Kohane: Hehe.
Kohane: (They must've really been looking forward to this day if they're this openly anxious about it.)
Kohane: (I can't wait either...)
Kohane: (I'm finally getting a chance to see a part of the reason why An and Shinonome want to surpass RAD WEEKEND as much as they do...!)
Taiga: Hey, you guys are early. We weren't supposed to meet for a while, you know?
Kohane: Hello, Taiga!
An: Of course we're here early! Two of us at least never thought we'd ever get to see COL again!
Toya: Thank you for creating this incredible opportunity for us today.
Toya: We definitely wouldn't have been able to do anything like this on our own.
Taiga: Heh. I'm glad you're happy, but this is about all I can show you guys at this point...
Taiga: The owner's waiting for us there, so let's start making our way over.
Kohane: Okay!
Taiga: Here it is. The basement for this building's COL.
An: Whoa, talk about a blast from the past... I totally remember lining up here to get in, and how the line spilled out onto the street...
Akito: Yeah, and three years have passed since...
Taiga: From the outside, it looks like any of the other dives you can find around here.
???: Just what exactly are you calling a dive...?
Taiga: Hey, Granny. See? As happy and healthy as ever, right?
Owner: I'm the owner of this place, not your “Granny”. Thirty years and you still refuse to learn any manners...
Kohane: Is this person really the owner, An...?
An: Yeah, it's her. She used to own and operate a bunch of live houses around here.
An: Dad and Uncle Taiga have known her since they were our age.
Kohane: I had no idea...! That's so cool.
An: I know, right? Anyway, long time no see!
Owner: Hm? Oh, if it isn't An. It's nice to see that the girl with a chip on her shoulder's grown up so much.
An: Heehee! It's nice to see you too!
Owner: Ah, you must be the one who's been aching to see my dive.
Kohane: Y-Yes, hello...! My name is Kohane Azusawa. I'm on the same team as An!
Kohane: W-We heard that you closed this place a long time ago, so thank you for being so kind as to show us around like this...!
Owner: I don't mind. I've been coming here from time to time to keep it clean.
An: Wait, really?
Owner: Well, I'm going to have to hand this place over to someone at some point... Not only that...
Owner: I'm sure actually being here will help you remember that night better.
Taiga: ...
Toya: That night... Is she referring to RAD WEEKEND?
Akito: Probably. Especially since this is where RAD WEEKEND happened.
Akito: It was probably the event she was looking for to cap off the history of this place.
Kohane: (So RAD WEEKEND meant a lot to the owner of this venue as well...)
Owner: Alright, let's head inside.
Kohane: Okay!
Kohane: (It's really where RAD WEEKEND happened... I have to absorb as much as I can...!)
Kohane: I-It's so dark...!
Toya: Our eyes haven't adjusted yet since it's so bright out today.
Akito: Just don't slip and fall, alright?
An: He's right. We need to watch where we walk.
Owner: Give me a second to turn on the floodlights.
Owner: Ah, here we go...
Kohane: Wow...!
Toya: So this is where RAD WEEKEND happened...
An: It's so much smaller than I remember.
Akito: Probably because we were kids. I'm guessing we were both a lot shorter back then.
An: Haha. That means we've grown up a lot since.
An: Still, the stage is literally right in front of us...
Kohane: (An and Shinonome seem completely awestruck...)
Kohane: (This is really it...)
Len: <Whoa! This is really the venue for RAD WEEKEND?!>
Kohane: Eep...! L-Len?!
Taiga: Hm? What's up?
Kohane: Um... N-Nothing!
Miku: <Len, you need to be quiet.>
Len: <O-Oh, right...!>
An: Kohane? Is something... Ah...
Miku: <Hehe. We're here. Sorry, we just couldn't wait.>
Akito: Hey, they'll see you if you keep jumping out like that. Wait until we give you the signal.
Len: <Hehe. Okay, I'm sorry... I'll be careful from now on.>
Miku: <We promise to stay hidden, so please let us see.>
Toya: I suppose you'll stay out of sight as long as you stay in Azusawa's pocket.
Kohane: Yeah, I'll try to position myself so that you both can get a good look.
Len: <Great! Thanks, Kohane!>
